    "The left vertical axis shows the subdomain size computed by each CPU and the right axis shows the actual parallel speedup; the x-axis shows the number of CPUs.",
    "We start our analysis from the top panel of Figure 9 with the setup of a medium domain size.",
    "The speedup is scaled with respect to 12 CPUs, which corresponds to a single full cluster node.",
    "Here, the strong scaling reveals several interesting aspects in its behavior.",
    "The first striking feature is that for a relatively small number of CPUs (< 2000) the code overperforms the ideal scaling exhibiting superlinear speedup (Gusev and Ristov, 2014)."
